  "local_port": 48378,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I'm doing my first pyromancer build in Dark Souls 3. What stats do I need to build on to be most effective?",
  "response": "Building an effective pyromancer in *Dark Souls 3* requires a balance of stats to maximize your fire and dark damage output while maintaining survivability. Here's a breakdown of the key stats to focus on:\n\n---\n\n### **Core Stats for Pyromancy**\n1. **Intelligence (INT)**  \n   - Pyromancies scale with both Intelligence and Faith, so INT is crucial. Aim for at least **40 INT** for optimal damage.\n\n2. **Faith (FTH)**  \n   - Like Intelligence, Faith also boosts your pyromancy damage. Aim for **40 FTH** to pair with your INT.\n\n3. **Attunement (ATT)**  \n   - Increases your Focus Points (FP) and the number of attunement slots for spells. Aim for **24-30 ATT** for a good balance of FP and slots.\n\n---\n\n### **Secondary Stats**\n4. **Vigor (VIG)**  \n   - Increases your health pool. Aim for **27-35 VIG** to survive tougher encounters.\n\n5. **Endurance (END)**  \n   - Increases stamina for casting spells, dodging, and attacking. Aim for **20-30 END** depending on your playstyle.\n\n6. **Vitality (VIT)**  \n   - Increases equip load for heavier armor and weapons. Invest only as much as needed to wear your desired gear while staying under 70% equip load.\n\n---\n\n### **Optional Stats**\n7. **Dexterity (DEX)**  \n   - Some pyromancer weapons (e.g., Onikiri and Ubadachi, Sellsword Twinblades) scale well with DEX. If you're using a weapon with DEX scaling, invest up to **16-20 DEX**.\n\n8. **Strength (STR)**  \n   - Some pyromancer weapons (e.g., Demon's Scar, Dark/Chaos-infused weapons) benefit from STR. Invest only as needed for your weapon choice.\n\n---\n\n### **Weapon Scaling**\n- Use **Chaos** or **Dark-infused weapons** for scaling with INT and FTH.\n- Examples: Chaos Longsword, Dark Carthus Curved Sword, Onyx Blade, Demon's Scar.\n\n---\n\n### **Starting Class**\n- **Pyromancer** is the best starting class, as it has balanced INT and FTH for pyromancy.\n\n---\n\n### **Soft Caps**\n- **INT/FTH**: Soft cap at 40/40 for pyromancy damage.\n- **ATT**: Soft cap at 30 for FP and slots.\n- **VIG**: Soft cap at 27 (1000 HP), diminishing returns after 40.\n\n---\n\n### **Recommended Build Example**\n- **SL 120 Build**:  \n  Vigor: 27  \n  Attunement: 24  \n  Endurance: 20  \n  Vitality: 10  \n  Strength: 12 (for weapon requirements)  \n  Dexterity: 16 (for weapon requirements)  \n  Intelligence: 40  \n  Faith: 40  \n  Luck: Base (7)\n\n---\n\n### **Key Pyromancies**\n- **Chaos Bed Vestiges**: High damage, great for bosses.\n- **Great Chaos Fire Orb**: AOE damage with lingering lava.\n- **Black Flame**: Close-range burst damage.\n- **Carthus Flame Arc**: Weapon buff for early game.\n\n---\n\n### **Rings**\n- **Great Swamp Ring**: Boosts pyromancy damage.\n- **Witch's Ring**: Further boosts pyromancy damage.\n- **Sage Ring**: Faster spellcasting.\n- **Fire Clutch Ring**: Increases fire damage (optional, but reduces defense).\n\n---\n\nBy focusing on these stats and gear, you'll be a formidable pyromancer capable of melting enemies with fire and dark magic!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
